	<div id="container">
		<video autoplay="true" id="videoElement">
		
		</video>
	</div>
	<script>
		var video = document.querySelector("#videoElement");
		if (navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia) {
		  navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({ video: true })
			.then(function (stream) {
			  video.srcObject = stream;
			})
			.catch(function (err0r) {
			  console.log("Something went wrong!");
			});
		}
	</script>
	<h1>Webcam Project Based On Machine Learning</h1>
	<h2>Group members: chengw4, salsh2, kasyeda2, ananyab3, cw72, hs38</h2>
	<p>Our project is web-based people detection through monitors in rooms such as lecture halls, to detect the number of people in a room to makes sure that the capacity follows COVID-19 guidelines and warn if not. Our current focus is using machine learning to train a model that detects people in the camera. In addition, we are creating web interface to connect the front-end and back-end for easily access. In the future, we may further train our model to recognize if people are wearing face masks and maintain social distance. </p>
	<form id='myform' action="welcom.php" method="post">
	<div class='msg'></div>
		building: <input type="text" id="building">
		room:&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp<input type="number" id="roomnumber">
		<button type="submit">access</button>
		<button type="reset">reset</button>
	</form>
	<script>
		const inputBuilding = document.querySelector('#building');
		const inputRoom = document.querySelector('#roomnumber');
		const myform = document.querySelector('#myform');
		const msg = document.querySelector('msg');
		myform.addEventListener('submit', onSubmit);
		function onSubmit(e) {
			e.preventDefault();
			if(inputBuilding === null || inputRoom === NaN) {
				msg.classList.add('error');
				msg.innerHTML = 'Please enter all fields';
			} else {
				console.log('success');
			}
		}
	</script>
